snippet.title: What's happening under the hood with C's type conversion rules? Go!
snippet.description:
Today's C dev challenge explores a common source of bugs. At first glance, -1 is clearly less than 1, but C's type conversion rules have something to say about that. What's happening under the hood, and which branch actually executes? 

Subscribe to Google for Developers → https://goo.gle/developers 

Speakers: Laurie Wu
